    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="815"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d815">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12449.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Carranza says a satisfactory understanding between all chiefs is assured.
                    Says he and his chiefs and people greatly appreciate the United States as their
                    great friends. Says he called his chiefs together and that they are all opposed
                    to treating with Huerta’s people and feel that the only way to permanent peace
                    is to fight it out and take Mexico City and the whole country. He says they want
                    the continued patience and sympathy of the United States extended to the end of
                    the fight. He asks that their northern boundary will be kept <pb facs="0677"
                        n="561" xml:id="pg_561"/> closed and that Tampico will be kept open to arms
                    and ammunition only when consigned to the First Chief.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
